what is all tax free for tax free weekend in ma it is one weekend a year that the legislature allows retailers to sell goods under a set figure for ex without charging sales tax the benefit to the consumer is saving the sales tax assuming retailers don't mark up prices the benefit to the retailer is increased sales during a slumping month typically july or aug the benefit to the state is although sales tax revenue is lost the holiday gets money out of people's savings accounts and into the economy to help economic growth Tax Microeconomics FairTax Value added tax Price discrimination Economy of Russia Wal-Mart Gross domestic product Tesco Inflation Economy of India Supply-side economics Tariff Free trade Economy of the United States Capitalism United Kingdom corporation tax Economy of Pakistan Privatization Progressive tax Externality Deflation (economics) Credit card Variable universal life insurance Protectionism Reaganomics Keynesian economics Economy of the Republic of Ireland Surplus value Monopoly Life insurance Annuity Supermarket Warren Buffett Economy of Chile Arthur Laffer Minimum wage Economy of Singapore London Congestion Charge Outsourcing Retailer Hyperinflation Tax cut Bank UK Singles Chart Social Security (United States) Public good Health insurance Labor-power Income trust Economy of Norway Economic Growth and Tax Relief Reconciliation Act of 2001 Celtic Tiger Consumer price index Filling station Inventory Galactic Civilizations Electronic commerce Marketing Oil price increases of 2004 and 2005 U.S. public debt Great Depression Canadian and American economies compared Goods and Services Tax (Canada) Economy of Romania Ford Motor Company California Proposition 13 (1978) Insurance Flat tax Measures of national income and output Alcohol fuel Social Security debate (United States) Public policy Subsidy Sales tax Money supply Commodity Economy of Lebanon Euro 401(k) Sears Holdings Corporation Black market Gold standard Publicly funded medicine Economic g